Governor Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia State has banned the collection of revenue along major roads to check activi­ties of touts in the state. Ikpeazu made the an­nouncement in a statement issued by his Chief Press Secretary, Onyebuchi Eme­manka, made available to newsmen in Aba on Satur­day. The governor noted that the activities of touts had increased in parts of the state due to the culture of revenue collection along major roads. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said that revenue col­lection along major roads had been hijacked by touts, who had become nuisance to residents. Ikpeazu further directed the chairman of Osisioma Ngwa Local Government Area, Christian Kamalu, to immediately rid the Osisio­ma flyover of touts to restore decency. Kaduna To Upgrade Hospitals With N4.6bn Instigating Regime Change Outside Ballot Box Unconstitutional, Call To Anarchy – FG “Henceforth, it has be­come illegal for any revenue agent to waylay or harass motorists or other road us­ers along major roads in the state. “The police and other law enforcement agencies have been told to enforce this directive, anybody found culpable will face the law,” he said. Activities of touts had re­mained visible in the state despite a law passed by the Abia House of Assembly, and the state government banning touting in 2016. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION